          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Artem Blagodarenko",
          "email": "artem_blagodarenko@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2012-01-30 16:48:18.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Artem Blagodarenko",
          "email": "artem_blagodarenko@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2012-04-02 11:42:19.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-903 ldlm: mdc lock inode reference moved to resource",
        "message": "LU-903 ldlm: mdc lock inode reference moved to resource\n\nThere is a race condition while get_attr after cancel_lru_locks\nand sysctl drop_caches. ll_clear_inode clears l_ast_data for\nldlm lock and this lock can't be canceled because \"inode == NULL\".\nll_mdc_blocking_ast finds such lock. As result DCACHE_LUSTRE_INVALID\nis not set and lookup returns wrong inode.\n\nThis patch moves inode structure reference to\n\"ldlm_lock::l_resource::lr_lvb_inode\". This prevents from different\ninode references for same resource's lock.\n\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-269\nReviewed-by: Vitaly Fertman <vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com>\nReviewed-by: Alexey Lyashkov <alexey_lyashkov@xyratex.com>\n\nSigned-off-by: Artem Blagodarenko <artem_blagodarenko@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: I65d8eb82c6fa88bb5a6d84b992236a3620423c44\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
